eds.ensemble module¶

class eds.ensemble.Ensemble(models: [] = None, names: [<class 'str'>] = None, weights: numpy.array = None)¶

Bases: abc.ABC

Base class for an sklearn model-like wrapper for an ensemble of models.

fit(X: numpy.array, Y: numpy.array) → None¶

Fits each of the models in the ensemble to the data. This is usually the last step and assumes the weights have been optimized already.

Xnp.array

Set of feature vectors.

Ynp.array

Set of respective outputs of the feature vectors.

abstract static get_default_models_names() → [<class 'str'>]¶
get_model_importances()¶

Returns a list of important models. Importance calculated using the weights. If names were not provided, simply returns the weights.

[]

Returns a list of important models.

optimal_fit_cv(X: numpy.array, Y: numpy.array) → None¶

Optimizes the weights of the vector using cross-validation, then fits to all of the data.

Set of feature vectors.

Ynp.array

Set of respective outputs of the feature vectors.

optimize_weights_cv(X: numpy.array, Y: numpy.array, iterations: int = 1000) → None¶

Optimizes the weights of the ensemble by using cross-validation.

predict(x: numpy.array) → numpy.array¶

Predicts classes of feature vectors with the ensemble. Note: Binary output is only supported at this time.

xnp.array

Set of feature vectors to predict classes for.

np.array

Ensemble’s prediction of binary classes.

predict_proba(x: numpy.array) → numpy.array¶

Predicts the class probability vector for the feature vectors with the ensemble.

xnp.array

Set of feature vectors.

np.array

Prediction for the classes probabilities for each feature vector.
